  "prompt": "How do I get accepted into Berklee College of music?",
  "response": "To increase your chances of getting accepted into Berklee College of Music, follow these steps:\n\n1. Academic Preparation\n- Maintain a strong high school GPA\n- Take music and advanced classes\n- Develop strong academic skills\n\n2. Musical Preparation\n- Develop exceptional musical skills in your chosen instrument/style\n- Practice consistently\n- Take private lessons\n- Participate in school or community music ensembles\n\n3. Audition Requirements\n- Prepare a strong audition repertoire\n- Choose pieces that showcase your technical and artistic abilities\n- Practice audition pieces extensively\n- Select appropriate repertoire for your instrument/major\n\n4. Application Process\n- Complete the online application\n- Submit all required documents\n- Pay application fee\n- Write a compelling personal statement\n- Highlight your musical achievements and passion\n\n5. Additional Recommendations\n- Attend Berklee summer programs\n- Participate in music workshops\n- Build a strong performance portfolio\n- Demonstrate musical versatility\n- Show dedication to musical growth\n\n6. Audition Preparation\n- Schedule an audition\n- Choose appropriate audition format (live or recorded)\n- Follow specific audition guidelines for your instrument\n- Present yourself professionally\n\n7. Scholarship Opportunities\n- Apply for merit-based scholarships\n- Submit additional scholarship applications\n\nDemonstrate passion, skill, and commitment to increase acceptance chances.",
